## When Docs, Code, And Previews Disagree

1. **These pages** describe the intended direction, including items on the [token list](<%= page_path("design-system-tokens") %>#whats-on-our-list).
2. **`pathogen.tailwind.css` and shipped components** are ground truth for behaviour and values not called out as future work.
3. **Previews** should prove the system in product-like contexts. Fix drift instead of creating a second visual language.

`Button` and `CopyableValue` are the clearest semantic-token examples today. New work should follow them instead of legacy `neutral-600` shortcuts.

## Host Applications

Pathogen owns shared roles, component behaviour, and accessibility expectations. Host apps own brand colour through `--color-primary-*` (Pathogen defaults to blue; IRIDA uses green). Local host components should still use Pathogen tokens and interaction patterns while they remain in use.
